      "writtenOn": "2018-06-12T18:18:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "My thinking is that the things being compared will have been generated in the same way (so two xforms to a linear destination will both have created the same negative 0s, etc). The long version might read nicer anyway? OF course, we memset the steps objects when we construct them, so I could replace this entire function with one memcmp()?",
